	<ns3301:title xmlns:ns3301="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Network Time Server</ns3301:title>
	<ns3302:para xmlns:ns3302="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
	A network time server allows to exactly synchronise all clients on a network's time from a central server. Each time server is part of a hierachy with a atomic clock, usually at the top of the hierachy, and all other servers ,synchronising their time from another server higher up in the hierachy. 
	</ns3302:para>
	<ns3303:para xmlns:ns3303="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
	This section covers the configuration of a standalone NTP server. For more information on this topic, visit (http://www.ntp.org).	
	</ns3303:para>
